
[1]bewail

   BEWA'IL, v.t. [be and wail.] To bemoan; to lament; to express sorrow
   for. It expresses deep sorrow; as, to bewail the loss of a child.

   The true penitent bewails his ingratitude to God.

                       BEWA'IL, v.i. To express grief.
